{{Sidebar("Glossary")}}

The **[same-origin policy](/blog/Web/Security/Same-origin_policy)** is a critical security mechanism that restricts how a document or script loaded from one {{Glossary("origin")}} can interact with a resource from another origin.

It helps isolate potentially malicious documents, reducing possible attack vectors.

